WEBVTT

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:05.538
Well, good evening, family. Thank you for joining us again tonight.

00:00:05.539 --> 00:00:09.960
We're excited to pray with y'all. We have some things I want to share with you.

00:00:09.961 --> 00:00:17.031
First, all glory to Jesus. We have no incidents today at all. And I just want to give God praise right now.

00:00:17.032 --> 00:00:22.990
I believe it's the fervent prayers of the righteous that avail much.

00:00:22.991 --> 00:00:34.727
It's because of you and me, and other prayer groups around the United States, that we're praying and changing things through the power of prayer and the authority of the believer.

00:00:34.728 --> 00:00:39.914
We're able to pray for the shopping, that there were no casualties. We only had one major incident.

00:00:39.915 --> 00:00:51.914
We pray for the family that lost their daughter in the tragic, terrible incident in Washington the day before Thanksgiving.

00:00:51.915 --> 00:00:56.873
That was awful. And she went home; I pray she knew Jesus Christ.

00:00:56.874 --> 00:01:01.293
That's why I try to tell you all the time, none of us are promised tomorrow.

00:01:01.294 --> 00:01:09.215
I'm sure she didn't know that day that she would pass away and that the tragic thing was going to happen.

00:01:09.216 --> 00:01:14.613
You never want to take this time for granted. Always look at the now.

00:01:14.614 --> 00:01:19.356
Thank God that we have now and give your heart to Jesus Christ.

00:01:19.357 --> 00:01:29.879
You must know Him. You must know that tomorrow's not promised. We pray for her family and for the loss.

00:01:29.880 --> 00:01:34.080
I don't know if she had children or what, but that was a very sad situation.

00:01:34.081 --> 00:01:44.297
I don't know if the other man passed away, but thank God it was not more. Thank God that today we didn't see anything.

00:01:44.298 --> 00:01:52.187
I still have an urgency to pray over the shopping all through this season.

00:01:52.188 --> 00:02:05.774
Continually praying over the economy, our nation, the nation's capital, and the White House tree ceremony with the lighting of the tree.

00:02:05.775 --> 00:02:23.833
Praying over the Rockefeller Times Square tree ceremony—that's why that's behind us tonight—and continually lifting up New Year's Eve and all the holiday season, that no weapon formed against this nation shall prosper.

00:02:23.834 --> 00:02:32.228
You always get the critics who say, 'Well, Brandon, don't you think we should have heard something?'No, 'no news is good news'in my opinion.

00:02:32.229 --> 00:02:35.274
I don't care if we ever hear. I'm still going to stand on the wall. I'm going to still yell.

00:02:35.275 --> 00:02:45.830
I'm going to tell you what's coming, what I see, and what the Lord keeps revealing to me: to pray for our nation and keep doing my job.

00:02:45.831 --> 00:02:59.112
I believe if we do see major things like we saw in Washington DC, where one person passed away—I don't know if the other one's still alive—but that's a prayer fail.

00:02:59.113 --> 00:03:07.353
We don't want anything to happen. I warned you the people have infiltrated this nation.

00:03:07.355 --> 00:03:19.134
And this guy, for all the things being said that he worked for the CIA and that the Trump administration pardoned him, I'm still looking into that.

00:03:19.135 --> 00:03:28.651
You don't know what's fake news and what's real news. So, I just try not to get into the conspiracies.

00:03:28.652 --> 00:03:40.756
I want to start off with this, and this is my opinion. Everything that I say about this is my opinion, and it's not me telling you to do anything.

00:03:40.757 --> 00:03:46.472
I want you to pray about everything I bring to you tonight and take it to God in prayer.

00:03:46.473 --> 00:03:58.859
It's not an act of fear or worry; it's just what my wife and I do. We believe this, but I do not bring it up very often.

00:03:58.860 --> 00:04:09.371
I talked to my mom on the phone today, and she was talking about some of the things she and my extended family do.

00:04:09.373 --> 00:04:22.500
I thought, 'Well, I don't like talking about this stuff because a lot of people do not agree with it, especially in the circles that we're in.'But I'm going to talk about it.

00:04:22.501 --> 00:04:33.599
I think it's wisdom sometimes just to present it. You do what you want with it, but that's what Diana and I do.

00:04:33.600 --> 00:04:40.239
You're like, 'What is it, Brandon? Oh my god, it's a conspiracy.'No.

00:04:40.240 --> 00:04:50.540
I want to talk to you about wheat and making homemade breads—shelf life for what I believe is coming.

00:04:50.541 --> 00:04:59.509
You don't have to do this, but this is what Diana and I do. We believe in making this wheat.

00:04:59.510 --> 00:05:12.136
It's just grains, but we've bought a mill and we make homemade breads. They're wheat berries.

00:05:12.137 --> 00:05:21.439
We send them through the mill and we make the bread because all the bread we get at the store has lost all its nutrients.

00:05:21.440 --> 00:05:33.913
It's trash. I'm just telling y'all, they bleach it. They do all kinds of terrible things to our breads; there are pesticides. We get this—it's organic. This is amazing stuff.

00:05:33.914 --> 00:05:55.218
If you have constipation issues, we have found that if you eat this on a regular basis, it really rubs the walls of your colon and causes you to have bowel movements.

00:05:55.219 --> 00:06:07.462
My daughter takes this wheat and she mills things for me: fresh muffins, fresh tortillas.

00:06:07.463 --> 00:06:20.907
This has shelf life for the end times. You don't ever have to worry. We had friends talk to us about it.

00:06:20.908 --> 00:06:33.323
I was asking God for an alternative to that survival food a big ministry in Branson sells.

00:06:33.324 --> 00:06:48.495
I was looking at the content inside these buckets, this 30-year shelf-life food, and in the natural, folks, you maybe could eat it for a couple of weeks, but it's not good for you.

00:06:48.496 --> 00:07:12.098
This stuff is bad. I know what the Father has told me is coming, and I know He's extended time and is doing things right by letting us pray for revival, but we all know the end times are coming.

00:07:12.099 --> 00:07:20.853
People always ask me, 'Brandon, do you believe in storing food back?'I don't like, like I said, the 30-year shelf-life food.

00:07:20.854 --> 00:07:36.318
It's not healthy. But wheat lasts if you have these tubs and tighten the lid to keep the oxygen off of it.

00:07:36.319 --> 00:07:46.448
You can grind up the wheat and make fresh breads to take care of your family.

00:07:46.449 --> 00:07:58.071
You can find YouTube videos if you search 'freshly milled flour'or 'freshly milled bread.'It talks about wheat berries, and a lot of people are doing it.

00:07:58.072 --> 00:08:15.279
So, there are a lot of instructional videos of how to do it. I try to think of how you stay alive and take care of yourself if things were to happen and the grid was to go down.

00:08:15.280 --> 00:08:29.237
Even for people who want to criticize, ', you said this, said that,'even FEMA and our government tell you to have at least a week's worth of food.

00:08:29.238 --> 00:08:33.155
That's not stupid; that's just being prepared. People get all bent out of shape.

00:08:33.156 --> 00:08:42.461
'Well, are you living in fear? You're not quoting the word.'No, I didn't say be stupid.

00:08:42.462 --> 00:08:47.189
I said have enough that your family can be taken care of in case of an emergency.

00:08:47.190 --> 00:08:55.216
Most people travel with a spare tire and jumper cables. Are you expecting to have a flat?

00:08:55.217 --> 00:09:02.111
But you have it. I'm not anticipating a flat, but you have the spare tire.

00:09:02.112 --> 00:09:05.912
I don't anticipate having one, but it's there for an emergency.

00:09:05.913 --> 00:09:14.754
I don't anticipate having a dead battery, but you have jumper cables because of the emergency or roadside assistance.

00:09:14.755 --> 00:09:20.993
For our insurance company, we buy extra for five bucks a month for AAA.

00:09:20.994 --> 00:09:33.011
Whenever you call them, they come. I pay for the insurance just in case. Life insurance is there just in case, if you can afford it.

00:09:33.012 --> 00:09:40.569
I don't anticipate dying, but if something were to happen, you want to make sure your family's taken care of. Life insurance is there.

00:09:40.570 --> 00:09:50.800
Sometimes you get really persecuted in the Word of Faith charismatic circle for saying some of the stuff I'm telling you, but I'm trying to warn you.

00:09:50.801 --> 00:10:05.492
I have seen a storm. We know that God is merciful and He'll take care of us, and we don't get in fear.

00:10:05.493 --> 00:10:17.359
The Lord showed us that we would pray over our pots of food and that there would be stuff appearing and that there'll be supernatural provision when there is no provision.

00:10:17.360 --> 00:10:24.781
But I believe you put your hand to the plow and you work, and God will bless your efforts.

00:10:24.782 --> 00:10:34.221
Joseph stored food for the famine. There were seven years of plenty and seven years not.

00:10:34.222 --> 00:10:41.246
He could have said, 'I don't really believe that.'What would have happened? So you just have to do what God tells you to do.

00:10:41.247 --> 00:10:47.181
This is just one instance people ask me about all the time because we eat it anyway.

00:10:47.182 --> 00:10:52.737
We love these muffins. It's not going to expire because we'll eat it before it does.

00:10:52.738 --> 00:10:58.967
She makes homemade cakes with this; she makes pie crust pastry.

00:10:58.968 --> 00:11:05.623
We make pie crusts and cakes and all kinds of things for birthdays.

00:11:05.624 --> 00:11:13.054
This is so much healthier than eating a sack of flour from Walmart. There are good nutrients in this.

00:11:13.055 --> 00:11:22.184
There are a lot of vitamins and minerals that they take out of your stuff because they mill it in the factory and bleach the flour.

00:11:22.185 --> 00:11:31.999
Number two, I was praying and I said, 'Lord, I don't like all of the vegetables and stuff from the store.

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:43.408
I like organic. Teach me because it doesn't have a long shelf life.'If you learn how to can... I had a lady named Sherry. She was into canning food.

00:11:43.409 --> 00:11:53.964
She learned how to can pot roast meals and stored her house full of that, which was pretty brilliant because she eats that.

00:11:53.965 --> 00:12:08.631
She's a friend of ours from the old church. You get ideas that God will give you to sustain things, and you can eat it and rotate it out so you always have extra.

00:12:08.632 --> 00:12:20.283
Then there are Tower Gardens. Now, Tower Gardens are very wise.

00:12:20.284 --> 00:12:30.061
We have two of them, and you can grow your vegetables from these Tower Gardens that have lights on them.

00:12:30.062 --> 00:12:35.803
You can have a backup in case the grid goes down that runs off solar power.

00:12:35.804 --> 00:12:47.085
Solar power runs outside your house a little bit during the day so these lights shine during the winter.

00:12:47.086 --> 00:12:59.537
They have little seed pods, and you can grow tomatoes, cucumbers, lettuce, cabbage, carrots, whatever.

00:12:59.538 --> 00:13:11.797
It grows out of this and has a base where the water is always filtering up through it and feeds the plants what they need to sustain life.

00:13:11.798 --> 00:13:23.617
If you do it right, it'll produce five pounds of food a week per garden. You go by how much your family may need.

00:13:23.618 --> 00:13:38.288
Some say, 'Our family would eat 20 pounds of vegetables a week,'which is a lot. Ten for us. That's if you're just eating a vegan diet.

00:13:38.289 --> 00:13:47.514
You can eat a lot of vegan with some bread and good grains and sustain your life.

00:13:47.515 --> 00:13:56.533
We're not vegan, but meat takes cold to stay fresh. It's hard to keep meat fresh if the grid's down.

00:13:56.534 --> 00:14:06.125
I have seen things about cyberattacks and electricity attacks where people are without this stuff for three and four weeks at a time.

00:14:06.126 --> 00:14:12.799
We're praying against it, but if it were to happen, how could you sustain your hamburger?

00:14:12.800 --> 00:14:28.517
How would you keep your freezer going? I have a generator. How long can you keep a generator going with gas or natural gas for a long period? You could run it every three hours, but what if it's longer?

00:14:28.518 --> 00:14:40.192
I don't like to get into this because it becomes controversial for a lot of people, but I felt in my heart to do it tonight, and you can take it for what you want.

00:14:40.192 --> 00:14:49.176
Having a Tower Garden running off solar and a battery generator... it's a little thing; it's a Jackery.

00:14:49.177 --> 00:14:56.554
They have all different kinds of brands, but it's one of those little ones.

00:14:56.555 --> 00:15:05.999
I think we do have a Jackery. It lasts hours, and you can run a microwave on it for four or five hours.

00:15:06.000 --> 00:15:27.923
I think we paid like 800 bucks for it, and you can run your Tower Garden off of it and keep your plants alive.

00:15:27.924 --> 00:15:34.933
I'm not telling you what you should do; I'm trying to tell you what we do because we eat it anyway.

00:15:34.934 --> 00:15:49.149
It's not fear. It's good to eat vegetables and fresh bread. This is sustainable.

00:15:49.150 --> 00:16:11.191
You can buy tubs of it, rotate it out, and I don't know how many loaves of bread you can make with this and muffins.

00:16:11.192 --> 00:16:19.999
This turns into a lot. It expands when you mill it. It's fluffier.

00:16:20.000 --> 00:16:25.038
It looks like very little, but when you grind it up, it turns into a lot.

00:16:25.039 --> 00:16:38.374
If that was already milled, it would be a lot bigger. This right here is for backup, for power.

00:16:38.375 --> 00:16:44.349
We're not selling the brand. I'm not trying to sponsor it; I'm just trying to tell you.

00:16:44.350 --> 00:16:56.061
There are a lot of different brands that are amazing, but this is the one we got, and we plug our stuff into it.

00:16:56.062 --> 00:17:06.111
We got it on sale off Amazon, maybe Black Friday, so they might have good deals going on right now.

00:17:06.112 --> 00:17:13.838
We got solar panels and it charges it. In case of emergency, you put the solar panel out and it keeps stuff going.

00:17:13.839 --> 00:17:20.879
I'm just trying to give alternative ideas for you. I don't like the 30-year shelf life food.

00:17:20.880 --> 00:17:27.197
I don't think it's healthy for the body of Christ. If you believe in it and you sell it, that's on you.

00:17:27.198 --> 00:17:37.384
I'm just trying to say: what are alternative ideas that could help you, things you're already consuming that aren't way out there?

00:17:37.385 --> 00:17:46.158
The next thing would be chickens. Now, I know Sister Billie and her ministry; they have 30 chickens or more.

00:17:46.159 --> 00:17:56.400
I mean, they have a lot of chickens. Her son Terry and the rest of them have chickens; they lay eggs out there, and they fish and hunt.

00:17:56.401 --> 00:18:05.624
But we live in the city, so you can't kill deer, hunt, and fish because we don't have a place to go.

00:18:05.625 --> 00:18:17.999
So, you have to think outside the box. If you live in a major city like Chicago or New York, what could you do in case of an emergency?

00:18:18.000 --> 00:18:26.642
I bring all this up for a reason, but I just don't get into it. There's much you do not know that I do not say, but that I pray over.

00:18:26.643 --> 00:18:33.182
I'm telling you now, there was a group of us in 2015 in our old church.

00:18:33.183 --> 00:18:44.016
We got all into survivalism, and people got into saving things back. People get real flaky with it.

00:18:44.017 --> 00:18:48.345
I never try to give advice, but I see these things and we pray over them.

00:18:48.346 --> 00:18:59.012
I had one YouTuber say, 'You're saying that you cost people their houses and everything.'No, they sold their houses to downsize because they thought the economy was going to crash.

00:18:59.013 --> 00:19:02.990
I didn't cause anybody to lose their house; it wasn't because of anything I said.

00:19:02.991 --> 00:19:09.036
They were already preppers and were downsizing their homes.

00:19:09.037 --> 00:19:13.469
Now, people try to say, 'Well, Brandon, you cost them their house.'I saw YouTube videos and I said, 'Are you kidding?

00:19:13.470 --> 00:19:20.262
I never cost anybody their house.'They sold their houses because of things that we were talking about and praying over.

00:19:20.263 --> 00:19:26.239
We were all in a prayer group; it's a church thing. It isn't on me. Adults are adults.

00:19:26.240 --> 00:19:31.225
If you're an adult, you put your big boy or big girl pants on; I'm not responsible for your household.

00:19:31.226 --> 00:19:35.225
But we pray. Now, if you're not a part of it, you automatically want to see...

00:19:35.226 --> 00:19:39.746
like the other pastors, they don't like some of the stuff you're saying because they're seeker-friendly.

00:19:39.747 --> 00:19:46.126
99% of the seeker-friendlies don't want to talk about this stuff, and they go, 'Well, you're causing fear.'So, shut up.

00:19:46.127 --> 00:19:49.297
We don't want you talking in our church anymore. That's fine.

00:19:49.298 --> 00:19:54.063
I have an opinion and I'm entitled to it, but I'm not telling you to do anything.

00:19:54.064 --> 00:20:08.433
This is what we do, and people have asked. The other part was coins. I like old silver coins that are tradable.

00:20:08.434 --> 00:20:22.938
Having things like this—this is a silver coin, an old coin from 1812.

00:20:22.939 --> 00:20:31.266
Old coins like that are junk silver. I always try to think outside the box regarding bartering.

00:20:31.267 --> 00:20:39.585
Well, if you have a chicken and I have a piece of silver, could I take this and barter with you to get a chicken?

00:20:39.586 --> 00:20:44.475
Because I like chicken. And you can make a pot of noodles with this wheat.

00:20:44.476 --> 00:20:54.621
You make noodles out of it, boil a chicken, and you have chicken noodle soup. It's all part of it.

00:20:54.622 --> 00:21:05.275
And if you have change—I've found a lot of spare change in the past that would have old coins, like quarters from 1964 and older.

00:21:05.276 --> 00:21:18.648
If you go on YouTube and search it, you'll see they're worth more than a quarter; they're worth a few dollars because they're still 90% silver.

00:21:18.649 --> 00:21:28.154
So, having junk silver for bartering and trading is good. The other part is firearms.

00:21:28.155 --> 00:21:36.681
I know it's controversial and people get upset with me, but I am a man who believes in the Second Amendment.

00:21:36.682 --> 00:21:46.529
I believe that we have the right to bear arms and the right to defend your family. I do not back away from it or shy away from it.

00:21:46.530 --> 00:21:55.666
I know there's a lot of Christians that get really upset at me about that, but my wife and I are very trained in protecting ourselves with our firearms.

00:21:55.667 --> 00:22:01.883
You come through my front door uninvited and you kick it in, you won't be here the next day.

00:22:01.884 --> 00:22:07.778
I'm just telling you where we are. Now, people don't like that, but that's the honest-to-God truth.

00:22:07.779 --> 00:22:12.946
You kick in my door, you're not going to be here. You come in and try to hurt me, you're going to go home early.

00:22:12.947 --> 00:22:18.691
I'll pray for you as you're dying, but you're going home. That's just the way it is.

00:22:18.692 --> 00:22:21.526
People don't like that, but that's just where Diana and I are.

00:22:21.527 --> 00:22:28.175
If that comes across to you like, 'Brandon, I can't believe you'd say that,'then this channel is not for you.

00:22:28.176 --> 00:22:34.956
We're just trying to help you. That's the way we were raised; that's southern.

00:22:34.957 --> 00:22:49.829
Even as a kid, we believed in shotguns, rifles, and AR-15s. I train my kids on how to shoot them. I know where we are in the last days.

00:22:49.830 --> 00:22:59.759
I believe in praying for you and I believe in raising the dead, but if you touch my family, it's another story.

00:22:59.760 --> 00:23:07.770
Don't mess with me. We pray for you and we love you, but you're not going to try to hurt us.

00:23:07.771 --> 00:23:20.299
We'll give you a blessing, we'll pray for you, and maybe make you a loaf of bread, but we're going to do that part of what God has divvied out.

00:23:20.300 --> 00:23:33.109
It's your job to hear God for yourself and to follow the Holy Ghost for yourself. It's not my job to babysit you.

00:23:33.110 --> 00:23:41.359
I try to tell people that all the time, but they ask me, 'Brandon, what do you believe about these certain things?'So, this is what I had for you tonight.

00:23:41.360 --> 00:23:45.419
We believe in the Second Amendment and the right to bear arms.

00:23:45.420 --> 00:23:50.479
We believe in storing up and protecting our family for what I know is coming.

00:23:50.480 --> 00:23:57.436
There is a storm coming, and many of you will not make it to the other side of that storm.

00:23:57.437 --> 00:24:07.048
I believe we will see the birthing pains of where we are before the coming of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:24:07.049 --> 00:24:14.639
Now, I know a lot of people do not want to hear that, but you need to.

00:24:14.640 --> 00:24:18.649
'Well, the rapture is coming, Brandon.'Yes, but we're in the beginning of sorrows.

00:24:18.650 --> 00:24:27.105
What do you think is going to come with those earthquakes in divers places, plagues, pestilence, wars, and rumors of wars?

00:24:27.106 --> 00:24:34.685
All these things are the beginning of sorrows, but the end is not yet.

00:24:34.686 --> 00:24:43.119
As I've tried to warn you about a plague coming, I saw the rioting.

00:24:43.120 --> 00:24:53.515
I saw them killing people and doing whatever they could to get what you had.

00:24:53.516 --> 00:24:59.216
That's why you don't tell everybody what you have or how much you have.

00:24:59.217 --> 00:25:05.968
This way you keep your family safe. I'm trying to warn you ahead of time.

00:25:05.969 --> 00:25:20.130
It's not bad to have a little bit extra, but I believe in healthy alternatives instead of the trash that people put back.

00:25:20.131 --> 00:25:27.321
Ramen noodles are bad for you; it's not good to eat that all the time.

00:25:27.322 --> 00:25:39.759
There are good alternatives for your health, like minerals and vitamins. The Lord has been on this health kick with me.

00:25:39.760 --> 00:25:43.798
I don't know how many people we've lost, but that's what we wanted to tell you tonight.

00:25:43.799 --> 00:25:55.819
Does anyone have any questions? I'll answer a couple. I'm not afraid of it, but I don't want you being bullies because of what we believe.

00:25:55.820 --> 00:26:00.558
That's just us, and some people don't believe that way. You can have a pot of beans.

00:26:00.559 --> 00:26:04.239
You can have some rice. I personally do not like a lot of rice.

00:26:04.240 --> 00:26:12.739
I like beans, but I like my vegetables. I like my eggs. I like a bowl of oatmeal.

00:26:12.740 --> 00:26:17.842
If I had to have it, oatmeal lasts a lot longer. And eggs, you have chickens.

00:26:17.843 --> 00:26:24.601
I am talking about Billy's boy. They have chickens. My mom and dad like chickens.

00:26:24.602 --> 00:26:30.406
People like chickens, but as I said, we do not have a place we can put chickens. We don't.

00:26:30.407 --> 00:26:38.702
And I am sure our neighbors would not like hearing a rooster crow in the morning, but you can have a community.

00:26:38.703 --> 00:26:41.824
Maybe it is like with our neighbor Mary Lynn and all these people.

00:26:41.825 --> 00:26:48.716
You go, it is good to have a community that thinks alike. You are watching out for each other's backs.

00:26:48.717 --> 00:26:54.084
If the grid were to go down and people were acting crazy, you would want to know who your neighbors are.

00:26:54.085 --> 00:27:01.439
Our neighbors are nice. You go, well, do you trust them? I do not trust anybody, quite frankly, if they do not know Jesus Christ.

00:27:01.440 --> 00:27:08.681
And even then, I do not even trust a lot of people. But you have to know who is around you. So, I do not know, folks.

00:27:08.682 --> 00:27:20.879
I just thought I would tell you I believe in having a long gun, a handgun, and a shotgun.

00:27:20.880 --> 00:27:25.385
And in our case, you say, well, why do you have the shotgun? For home defense.

00:27:25.386 --> 00:27:32.405
