Billy asked me to do some things maybe, and I've been praying about that, doing prayer and things.

03:19:25.541 --> 03:19:32.233
I don't know if he wanted me to do it with him or whatever, but I never think about it.

03:19:32.234 --> 03:19:37.388
Would you even show up if I had it? I mean, I don't want to be the only one there.

03:19:37.389 --> 03:19:43.083
You go, 'Brandon has a meeting,'and nobody comes. You're out there by yourself and there's two people there.

03:19:43.084 --> 03:19:57.898
I'll be like, 'Well, we would still have fun.'I'm there no matter how many people are there as long as the Holy Spirit's there.

03:19:57.899 --> 03:20:08.902
'Lock down anytime'—CTF, what does that mean? 'Lock down anytime'is that they only had like 10 people in the service and it was Holy Ghost amazing.

03:20:08.903 --> 03:20:18.639
How do you know what God has called me to do? How do you know the mission God has for me?

03:20:18.640 --> 03:20:31.599
What bothers you the most? What are you passionate about? Does sickness bother you the most?

03:20:31.600 --> 03:20:38.559
Does pastoral stuff bother you the most? What drives you inside?

03:20:38.560 --> 03:20:47.677
God gives you the desires of your heart. The lost would be pastoral type stuff.

03:20:47.678 --> 03:20:57.224
He pushed those desires there. So that's what I go by. Prayer was something that I was drawn to.

03:20:57.225 --> 03:21:02.646
I was hungry for it. So I do healing, evangelism, things like that.

03:21:02.647 --> 03:21:06.248
I went to Benny Hinn. I went to those meetings. I was drawn to it.

03:21:06.249 --> 03:21:17.679
It was the glory. I wanted the presence. I wanted something authentic.

03:21:17.680 --> 03:21:26.112
How did you leave your full-time job? I feel God's calling in my ministry but don't know how to go about it.

03:21:26.113 --> 03:21:37.131
Thank you. Find you like eBay. We still do it; we haven't let eBay go. We're doing full-time.

03:21:37.132 --> 03:21:41.486
