03:22:28.450 --> 03:22:33.781
Like say you get a hoodie all the time—I'll flip it, I'll put it on eBay and I'll sell it.

03:22:33.782 --> 03:22:39.838
But I don't tell you my accounts because I don't want you to be weird and buy it and get bad feedback.

03:22:39.839 --> 03:22:46.238
So I don't tell a lot of people my accounts. I look at this as just another means to make money.

03:22:46.239 --> 03:22:49.479
You get it for a good deal or you find it on eBay and you flip it.

03:22:49.480 --> 03:22:54.398
You find a good thrift store and I find stuff, and I don't keep it.

03:22:54.399 --> 03:23:03.376
That's why you don't see me wear a lot of things twice, because Diana and I are always thinking how can you get things and flip them?

03:23:03.377 --> 03:23:08.048
But you always look nice and sharp on the video. We find things thrifting a lot.

03:23:08.049 --> 03:23:16.033
Yes. And Lululemon and things like that sell for cheap. You can find them at thrift stores—it's amazing.

03:23:16.034 --> 03:23:24.192
I always find things and people get mad. 'What brand do you wear?'I wear a lot of Lululemon t-shirts because they flip.

03:23:24.193 --> 03:23:29.438
Yeah, they're liberal, but whatever. It's a color. I try not to get into all that stuff.

03:23:29.439 --> 03:23:38.996
You can't wear nothing. 'Polo's liberal; all these people are going to hell.'I mean, it's just the world.

03:23:38.997 --> 03:23:45.226
Are you done? You pretty bored? I don't want it. Block the trolls, please.

03:23:45.227 --> 03:23:54.230
What trolls, son? I think you really are enjoying this chat.

03:23:54.231 --> 03:23:58.397
Well, I never get to see this part of it. He's getting really into it.

03:23:58.398 --> 03:24:03.696
I'm just going, 'Look at all this going on over here. This is like a party.'There's even more.

03:24:03.697 --> 03:24:07.943
There's only 4,600 people there. So they all went home. They're like, 'We're bored.

03:24:07.944 --> 03:24:17.095
